  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Executive (Marine Claims)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Attend to telephone enquiries and walk-in customers. Liaise with clients, intermediaries, surveyors/adjustors, handling agents, overseas Principals and TM Group of Companies.</li>\n  <li>Manage correspondence and attend meetings with clients/intermediaries when required.</li>\n  <li>Upon claims notification, gather relevant customers' details, arrange surveys and contact settling agents if needed.</li>\n  <li>Create claim files/checklist and check policy/reinsurance/treaty arrangements before confirming  underwriting accpetance with TM Group of Companies.</li>\n  <li>Send Acknowledgment Letter and request necessary claims documents from clients/intermediaries.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and dispatch PLA/Cash-Call Advice; follow up with reinsurers for payments.</li>\n  <li>Draft LLA/MLR for approval and ensure reserves are timely and accurate.</li>\n  <li>Maintain and review diary dates of 'live' files and ensure proper bring-up dates before archiving.</li>\n  <li>Verify premium payment before processing claims and liaise with Finance on payment delays.</li>\n  <li>Forward claims with strong recovery prospects to Claims Recovery Agents and actively follow up on recovery action. </li>\n  <li>Update records for exceptional claims (e.g. ex-gratia payments, large losses) and related recoveries.</li>\n  <li>Review and escalate claims exceeding authority to HOD/Senior Management for approval before notifying Customers, Settling Agents, etc. </li>\n  <li>Review files regularly, compile monthly/quarterly statistics as needed</li>\n  <li>Conduct UAT for Marine Claims module. </li>\n  <li>Carry out duties assigned by management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree holders in Insurance, Maritime Studies or related discipline;</li>\n  <li>Preferably ACII/AAII, CGI qualifications or relevant insurance equivalent;</li>\n  <li>Good working knowledge of Microsoft Office application; </li>\n  <li>Relevant experience will be an added advantage;</li>\n  <li>Possess good interpersonal and communications skills; </li>\n  <li>Able to multi-task, is a team player, conscientious, tactful, customer-focused and willingness to learn new skills. </li>\n</ul>",
